The following steps explain how to replicate this project. These instructions assume the user has basic familiarity with Python but has not previously run this pipeline.

# 1. Install Required Software  
To run this project, install the following tools:
- Python: download and install Python (version 3.9 or newer)
- Git: Git allows you to clone the project repository 
- VS code: provides the environment for editing scripts and running the pipeline 

# 2. Download the Repository
- Option 1: Using Git, open a new terminal in VS code and paste the code: git clone https://github.com/ashleyjmck22-hash/cardinals-ticket-weather-pipeline.git
then move into into the project folder by pasting this code in the terminal: cd cardinals-ticket-weather-pipeline
- Option 2: without Git, Go to the GitHub repository and click code and download ZIP, extract the folder locally.

# 3. Install Required Python Libraries 
- In the terminal in VS code install the required packages using pip, paste this code in the terminal:pip install pandas requests openpyxl

# 4. Add the Input Datasets 
- Place the provided ticket activity dataset into the following folder: data/raw/

